<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1227,1794]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1659,1686]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Comments.</emphasis>
Only four species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hendel" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1920" box="[705,991,1659,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Pseudonapomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[705,901,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Pseudonapomyza</emphasis>
Hendel
</taxonomicName>
are known in the New World, most of them in the Nearctic Region. 
<taxonomicName box="[498,793,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Pseudonapomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">
<emphasis box="[498,793,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Pseudonapomyza asiatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species recorded in the Neotropical Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Boucher, S." box="[159,323,1731,1758]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="781 - 791" refId="ref18116" refString="Boucher, S. (2004) The New World fauna of the genus Pseudonapomyza (Diptera: Agromyzidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 136, 781 - 791. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / n 03 - 121" type="journal article" year="2004">Boucher 2004</bibRefCitation>
). It is also widely distributed in the Old World, and is a leaf-miner of several 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1268,1732,1758]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, K. A." pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 444" refId="ref21140" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1990) Host specialization in the Worl Agromyzidae (Diptera). Series Entomologica, 45, i-xii + 1 - 444. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 009 - 1874 - 0" type="journal article" year="1990">Spencer 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
